description = Retrieve, capture, or refresh distilled agent-architectures knowledge — control flow and orchestration for agents: workflows vs an autonomous loop, ReAct and planning loops, reflection, routing and handoffs, single vs multi-agent, orchestrator-worker topologies, sub-agent delegation, and the control envelope (termination, verification, budgets). Use when deciding how an agent should be structured — whether to loop, reflect, route, or fan out, and when it stops — or looking up or saving an agent-architectures pattern — not when implementing the loop driver, tool dispatch, retries, sandboxing, or state persistence that execute it (that is agent-runtime).
